      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: allow fallback on prompt-stage harness-owned timeouts",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes #95574\n\nWhen a harnessOwnsTransport provider (Ollama, OpenRouter) times out during a prompt, the failover policy returns `surface_error` immediately, bypassing the fallback chain entirely. This defeats the purpose of configured fallbacks for local model ? cloud fallback scenarios.\n\n**Before:** Ollama timeout ? hard error \"LLM request timed out\", no fallback tried\n**After:** Ollama timeout ? rotate profile ? fallback to next model in chain\n\n## Evidence\n\n- All 32 tests in `failover-policy.test.ts` pass (verified locally with vitest)\n- The fix adds a single guard `!params.fallbackConfigured` to the prompt-stage timeout check\n- When no fallback is configured, behavior is unchanged (surface_error)\n- When fallback IS configured, the code falls through to the existing fallback check\n- Diff: 2 files changed, 8 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)\n\n## Root Cause\n\nIn `resolveRunFailoverDecision`, the `harnessOwnsTransport && failoverReason === \"timeout\"` check returns `surface_error` before the `fallbackConfigured` check is reached. The fix adds `&& !params.fallbackConfigured` so the early return only fires when no fallback is configured.",
